text: Frank Edward "Ted" Moss (September 23, 1911 - January 29, 2003) was an American lawyer and politician. He was a member of the Democratic Party. He was a United States Senator from Utah from 1959 to 1977. ==References== Category:1911 births Category:2003 deaths Category:Lawyers from Salt Lake City, Utah Category:United States senators from Utah Category:American military personnel of World War II Category:Politicians from Salt Lake City, Utah Category:Democratic Party (United States) politicians Category:Military people from Utah
